tion for w ≤ 5 (fast), fall back to MitM for w > 5.\n\nThis is the RIGHT approach! Let me implement it:\n\n**Check if vector v is in null space**: In RREF, the null space is the set of vectors satisfying:\n- For each pivot row r with pivot column p: `v[p] = sum_{free k: a[r][k]=1} v[freeCols[k]] (mod 2)`\n\nIn other words, `v` is a null vector iff for each pivot column p:\n`v[p] XOR (XOR over {k free: augRows[colToRow[p]][k] = 1 and k ≠ p} ∩ {k: v[k]=1}) = 0`\n\nThis simplifies to: `v` is in null space iff it satisfies RREF back-substitution with zero RHS.\n\nLet me rewrite the toggle solver to use this approach:"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":557,"cache_read_input_tokens":156414,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":557},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"650425f4-6a8c-484a-b0c6-6795964399da","uuid":"5bec61d6-d1a7-4ce9-b61d-de4c7680aa67"}
